a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:3;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:3:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:59;s:5:"title";s:88:"Bird app introduces native language support with browser detection and manual selection";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-app-introduces-native-language-support-with-browser-detecti/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-app-introduces-native-language-support-with-browser-detecti/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769582671;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769582666;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1139:"<p>Bird Platform added native multilingual support to the Bird app, enabling the interface to display in different languages without separate installations or plugins.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>The app now detects preferred language from browser settings and renders the UI in that language when supported.</p>
<p>Bird says static UI text is translated with locale-aware formatting rules (currency, pluralization, and number formatting).</p>
<p>Supported languages</p>
<ul>
<li>Portuguese (Portugal)</li>
<li>Portuguese (Brazil)</li>
<li>Dutch (Netherlands)</li>
<li>French (France)</li>
<li>German (Germany)</li>
<li>Spanish (Spain)</li>
<li>Russian (Russia)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Manual control</h3>
<p>Users can set a preferred language inside Bird via Profile → Language. If set, it takes priority over browser language.</p>
<h3>Known limitation</h3>
<p>Some dynamically loaded/API-driven content—such as custom pages and dashboards—may not yet be translated. Bird says translation coverage will expand over time.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://bird.com/en-us/updates">https://bird.com/en-us/updates</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:204:"Bird Platform added native multilingual support to the Bird app, enabling the interface to display in different languages without separate installations or plugins. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:204:"Bird Platform added native multilingual support to the Bird app, enabling the interface to display in different languages without separate installations or plugins. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:4:"bird";s:4:"href";s:34:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/bird/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:33:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:45:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:99:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-app-introduces-native-language-support-with-browser-detecti/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:103:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-app-introduces-native-language-support-with-browser-detecti/#comments";}i:1;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:13;s:5:"title";s:71:"Bird Platform updates default permissions for Contacts and CRM access";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-platform-updates-default-permissions-for-contacts-and-crm-a/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-platform-updates-default-permissions-for-contacts-and-crm-a/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1767712956;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1767712950;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1044:"<p>Bird Platform updated its default permission model for Contacts and CRM data to reduce unnecessary access across workspaces.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>Previously, Contacts and CRM access was included in base permissions for all users. Now, this access is not granted by default and requires a specific role.</p>
<h3>Who is affected</h3>
<p>Developer-only users: Contacts and CRM access is removed.</p>
<p>Marketing, Inbox, or CRM role users: No change; access continues.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>This is a shift toward least-privilege access: users only see Contacts/CRM data if their assigned role requires it. In practice, some teams may see access-related friction until roles are updated.</p>
<h3>How to regain access</h3>
<p>If you need Contacts/CRM access but only have the Developer role, an Organization Admin must assign an additional role (Marketing, Inbox, or CRM) alongside Developer.</p>
<p>Read an original article: <a href="https://bird.com/en-us/updates">https://bird.com/en-us/updates</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:175:"Bird CRM Platform updated its default permission model for Contacts and CRM data to reduce unnecessary access across workspaces. | Read fresh news about CRM on the WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:175:"Bird CRM Platform updated its default permission model for Contacts and CRM data to reduce unnecessary access across workspaces. | Read fresh news about CRM on the WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:4:"bird";s:4:"href";s:35:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/bird/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:8:"platform";s:4:"href";s:39:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/platform/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:99:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-platform-updates-default-permissions-for-contacts-and-crm-a/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:103:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-platform-updates-default-permissions-for-contacts-and-crm-a/#comments";}i:2;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:8;s:5:"title";s:66:"Bird Improves Navigation, Adds Learn Hub, and Fixes Key UI Issues";s:4:"href";s:86:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-crm-navigation-update-learn-hub-ui-fixes-april-2025/";s:13:"href-original";s:86:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-crm-navigation-update-learn-hub-ui-fixes-april-2025/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1747142109;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1747142092;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1084:"<p><a href="https://bird.com/">Bird CRM’s</a> latest update brings better navigation, easier access to help resources, and improvements across reporting and segmentation tools.</p>
<p>A key highlight is the new Learn hub a centralized section that combines Documentation, Support, Feedback, What’s New, and the Knowledge Base into one place.</p>
<p>The main navigation menu is now easier to use. Hovering over icons shows full menu names, helping users discover features faster. The layout has also been reorganized:</p>
<ul>
<li>“Log out” and “Switch workspace” are now in the Home menu</li>
<li>“Inbox” is renamed to “Support” for better clarity</li>
<li>Fixes in this update include:</li>
<li>Email Editor: Adding spaces in text blocks now works correctly</li>
<li>Segmentation: Fixed issues with the “is on” date operator</li>
<li>Reporting: Journey reports now show full numbers without cutting off values</li>
</ul>
<p>This update focuses on making Bird more intuitive and helping teams find what they need — when they need it.</p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:153:"Bird CRM improves navigation with a reorganized menu and hover labels, adds a Learn hub, and fixes email editor, segmentation, and reporting issues.";s:12:"snippet-text";s:153:"Bird CRM improves navigation with a reorganized menu and hover labels, adds a Learn hub, and fixes email editor, segmentation, and reporting issues.";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:2:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:4:"bird";s:4:"href";s:35:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/bird/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:91:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-crm-navigation-update-learn-hub-ui-fixes-april-2025/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:95:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/bird-crm-navigation-update-learn-hub-ui-fixes-april-2025/#comments";}}s:11:"pages_ctree";a:5:{s:9:"timeline?";b:1;s:5:"count";i:1;s:4:"this";i:1;s:13:"earlier-title";s:7:"Earlier";s:11:"later-title";s:5:"Later";}}